### INSTRUCTION
Please convert the following context into an SPARQL query.

### CONTEXT:
What are the anatomical entities where the human gene APOC1 is expressed in the post-juvenile stage? Provide also the taxon scientific name and the taxon common name and the strain label and the gene identifier.

### SPARQL:ampionship  ?strain ?taxon ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?taxon_scientificname ?gene ?taxon_commonname ?gene_identifier.

### ANSWER:
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?strain ?taxon ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?taxon_scientificname ?gene ?taxon_commonname ?gene_identifier WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?gene genex:isExpressedIn ?anatomicalentity.
	?gene rdfs:label "APOC1" .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity .
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	### Species: human.
	?gene orth:organism ?taxon .
	?taxon a up:Taxon .
	?taxon up:scientificName "human" .
	?taxon <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/scientificName> ?taxon_scientificname.
	?taxon <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/commonName> ?taxon_commonname.
	?strain a genex:Strain .
	?strain genex:hasLabel ?gene .
	?gene orth:organism ?strain .
	?strain <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/label> ?gene_identifier.
} ORDER BY DESC(?gene_identifier)

### Description:
This query provides the anatomical entity where the human gene APOC1 is expressed in the post-juvenile stage.

PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?cellType ?efo_0000399_label ?expressioncondition ?organism ?taxon ?anatomicalentity_label ?anatomicalentity_description ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?cellTypeName ?efo_0000399 ?score ?expression ?taxon_scientificname ?efo_0000399_description ?gene ?taxon_commonname ?gene_identifier WHERE {

	?expression genex:hasExpressionLevel ?score .

	?gene rdfs:label "APOC1" .

	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?anatomicalentity .
